  "doc_id": "12955",
  "text": "The present study reveals a new mechanism by which plasma protein affects the structural stability of the endothelial glycocalyx. Previous studies suggested that the negative charges on GAGs interacted with positively charged arginine residues on albumin to provide a stabilizing electrostatic interaction that was disrupted when protein was removed, leading to a collapse of the overall glycocalyx structure [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The new mechanism is quite different, centering on S1P binding to its S1P 1 receptor to inhibit protease activity-dependent shedding of the syndecan-1 ectodomain.",
